Part 1: CSS Basics - Selectors, Properties, and Values (20 Points)
In this part, we'll use element selectors, class selectors, and ID selectors to style different elements.

HTML:
html
Copy code
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>CSS Basics</title>
    <style>
        /* Element Selector */
        h1 {
            font-size: 30px;
        }

        /* Class Selector */
        .section {
            background-color: lightblue;
        }

        /* ID Selector */
        #unique {
            border: 2px solid black;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <h1>Heading 1</h1>
    <p>This is a paragraph.</p>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>This is a section with background color</h2>
        <p>More content here...</p>
    </div>

    <div id="unique">
        <h3>This is an element with a border</h3>
        <p>Details about the element...</p>
    </div>

</body>
</html>


e, Internal, and External CSS (30 Points)
Inline CSS (Change text color):
html
Copy code
<p style="color: green;">This paragraph has inline CSS that changes the text color to green.</p>
Internal CSS (Inside <style> tag in <head>):
html
Copy code
<head>
    <style>
        /* Style for all paragraphs */
        p {
            color: blue;
        }

        /* Style for all headings */
        h1, h2, h3 {
            font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif;
        }

        /* Style for all divs */
        div {
            padding: 20px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
External CSS (Link to an external file):
Create an external CSS file called styles.css:
css
Copy code
/* styles.css */

body {
    background-color: lightgray;
}

a:hover {
    color: red;
    text-decoration: underline;
}
Link the external CSS file to your HTML:
html
Copy code
<head>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
</head>
Part 3: Basic Styling Properties (50 Points)
In this part, we'll apply colors, font styles, text alignment, and spacing, and create a simple card component.

HTML:
html
Copy code
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Basic Styling</title>
    <style>
        /* Colors */
        p {
            color: #333;
            background-color: #f4f4f4;
        }

        h1 {
            color: darkblue;
        }

        /* Font Styles */
        h1 {
            font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif;
            font-size: 36px;
            font-weight: bold;
        }

        /* Text Alignment */
        p {
            text-align: justify;
        }

        /* Spacing (Padding and Margin) */
        .card {
            padding: 20px;
            margin: 15px;
            background-color: #ffffff;
            border: 1px solid #ddd;
            border-radius: 10px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <h1>Welcome to My Website</h1>
    <p>This is a paragraph that explains the content of the website. The text is justified to ensure it's aligned neatly.</p>

    <!-- Card Component -->
    <div class="card">
        <h2>Card Title</h2>
        <p>This is a simple card description with some content. The card has padding inside, and margin around it.</p>
    </div>

</body>
</html>
